<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FF87FFDD6DC2FB49FF65AE5D" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFF87FFDD6DC2FB49FF65AE5D" blockId="35.[178,1086,1236,1375]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">
Diagnosis: Within 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FF87FFDD6CBDFB49FDCEAFEB" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1876" box="[461,603,1236,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarandocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="1555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FF87FFDD6CBDFB49FDCEAFEB" box="[461,603,1236,1257]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Tarandocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there are two species, 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FF87FFDD6E02FB48FC76AFE8" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2015" box="[882,995,1237,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarandocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auratus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FF87FFDD6E02FB48FC76AFE8" box="[882,995,1237,1258]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">T. auratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FF87FFDD6958FB48FE88AE05" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarandocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FF87FFDD6958FB48FE88AE05" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">T. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whose members have the pronotal disc densely covered with gold-colored setae. But, in 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FF87FFDD6C4EFA92FE32AE26" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2015" box="[318,423,1295,1316]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarandocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auratus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FF87FFDD6C4EFA92FE32AE26" box="[318,423,1295,1316]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">T. auratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens the basal third of the pronotal disc is only infuscated, whereas in specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FF87FFDD6CCDFAB1FDD3AE43" box="[445,582,1324,1345]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarandocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FF87FFDD6CCDFAB1FDD3AE43" box="[445,582,1324,1345]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">T. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the basal third of the elytral disc is completely black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FF87FFDA6DC2FAF0FE8DAA85" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="1549" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548" type="description">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFF87FFDA6DC2FAF0FEB2AA2A" blockId="35.[178,1086,1389,1607]" lastBlockId="36.[178,1086,218,296]" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="1549" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">
Description: Size: Length 19.0 mm; width 8.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6EEAFAF0FC67AE81" box="[922,1010,1389,1411]" captionStart="Figs 169-172" captionStartId="54.[178,218,1509,1531]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1491]" captionTargetId="figure-58@54.[178,1085,212,1491]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Figs 169-172: Habitus illustrations of (169) Tarandocerus auratus, holotype; 170) T. lycoides, lectotype; (171) T. mexicanus, holotype; (172) T. testaceiceps, lectotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282525" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282525/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 169</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium mostly dark brown, vertex with a slightly visible flavotestaceous streak; pronotum flavotestaceous, vested with gold-colored setae; elytra bicolored, anterior third infuscated, posterior third of disc black, with very broad middle flavotestaceous fascia. Head: Basal antennomere of antennal capitulum (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6FDEFA40FD6DAEF1" box="[686,760,1501,1523]" captionStart="Figs 81-86" captionStartId="22.[178,218,1223,1245]" captionTargetBox="[192,1067,240,1173]" captionTargetId="figure-1@22.[178,1085,212,1205]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 81-86: Antennae. (81) Platynoptera ochreata, female; (82) Artoadenus similus, male; (83) Tarandocerus auratus, male; (84) T. mexicanus, male; (85) T. testaceiceps, male; (86) Pilosirus versus, female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294868/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
) as long as combined length of funicular antennomeres, antennomeres 9 and 10 with short collateral branch; antennal carina very prominent; EW/FW 25/33. Thorax: Pronotal anterior margin not projected at middle; side margin of disc slightly rounded at middle; PW/PL 105/115; elytra conspicuously flared; disc with 3 prominent discal carinae; EL/EW 420/130. Abdomen: Male pygidium not incised at distal margin; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF80FFDA6E7AFF6BFC3FAA0E" box="[778,938,245,268]" captionStart="Figs 133-144" captionStartId="40.[178,218,1358,1380]" captionTargetBox="[207,1052,231,1340]" captionTargetId="figure-1@40.[178,1084,212,1340]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figs 133-144: Aedeagi (133-140), Pronota (141-142), and Female mesodermal female reproductive organs (143-144). (133) Artoadenus similus phallus; (134) A. similus tegmen; (135) Tarandocerus auratus phallus; (136) T. auratus tegmen; (137) T. mexicanus phallus; (138) T. mexicanus tegmen; (139) T. testaceiceps phallus; (140) T. testaceiceps tegmen; (141) Pilosirus amazonicus; (142) P. versus; (143) Ambonoides retinoides female internal reproductive organs; (144) A. retinoides bursal plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294880" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294880/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="1549">Figs. 135, 136</figureCitation>
; tegmen well sclerotized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFF80FFDA6DC2FEAAFE8DAA85" blockId="36.[178,1085,311,391]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1549">
Variation: Size: Length 16.0-19.0 mm; width 6.0-8.0 mm. The black infuscation behind the humeral margin varies in expression. It is completely missing in 
<specimenCount id="42C3C782FF80FFDA6968FEC9FE81AA85" pageId="36" pageNumber="1549" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FF80FFDA6DC2FE0AFDB5AACB" pageId="36" pageNumber="1549" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFF80FFDA6DC2FE0AFDB5AACB" blockId="36.[178,1085,407,458]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1549">
Distribution (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF80FFDA6CEDFE0AFE6FAAAF" box="[413,506,407,429]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[178,210,1479,1501]" captionTargetBox="[178,1074,231,1457]" captionTargetId="figure-1@56.[178,1085,212,1470]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 174: Geographic distribution of species as noted." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282533" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282533/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="1549">Fig. 174</figureCitation>
): This species is known only from 
<collectingCountry id="2CD24C9BFF80FFDA6E03FE0AFC51AAAF" box="[883,964,407,429]" name="Mexico" pageId="36" pageNumber="1549">México</collectingCountry>
. Specimens are deposited in MNHN and WOPC
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
